Class EMP

java.lang.Object
edu.ucr.cs.pyneapple.regionalization.EMP
All Implemented Interfaces:
RegionalizationMethod
public class EMP extends Object implements RegionalizationMethod
EMP implements the algorithm for solving the Expressive Max-p Regions problem

  • Constructor Details

    • EMP

      public EMP()
      The default constructor of EMP. The default number of iterations for the construction phase is set to 10 and the limit of merge attempts is set to be 3

    • EMP

      public EMP(int its, int merges)
      The constructor of EMP that sets the number of iterations and the limit of merge attempts.
      Parameters:
      its - The number of iterations. The best result of all iterations is saved.
      merges - The limit of merge attempts when combining regions for the non-monitonic constraints. A small value tries to avoid growing oversized regions but more areas may remain unassigned.

  • Method Details

    • getP

      public int getP()
      Returns the number of regions. The function should be called after the regionalization analysis is initialized by invoking execute_regionalization(), otherwise returns -1.
      Specified by:
      getP in interface RegionalizationMethod
      Returns:
      the number of regions. -1 if the region partition is not initialized.

    • getRegionLabels

      public int[] getRegionLabels()
      Returns the region lael of each area. The function should be called after the regionalization analysis is initialized by invoking execute_regionalization(), otherwise returns {-1}.
      Specified by:
      getRegionLabels in interface RegionalizationMethod
      Returns:
      an array for the region label of each area. {-1} if the region partition is not initialized.

    • execute_regionalization

      public void execute_regionalization(Map<Integer,Set<Integer>> neighborSet, ArrayList<Long> disAttr, ArrayList<Long> sumAttr, Long threshold)
      Implements the execute_regionalization function of the RegionalizationMethod interface. The function performs the max-p regionalization.
      Specified by:
      execute_regionalization in interface RegionalizationMethod
      Parameters:
      neighborSet - A hashmap. The key is the area id of each area. The value is the set of id of the neighbor areas of the given area.
      disAttr - The list of dissimilarity attributes
      sumAttr - The list of attributes for the summation constraint.
      threshold - The lower-bound threshold for the max-p regions

    • execute_regionalization

      Performs the expressive regionalization. The results can be accessed through the get functions.
      Parameters:
      neighborSet - A hashmap. The key is the area id of each area. The value is the set of id of the neighbor areas of the given area.
      disAttr - The list of dissimilarity attributes
      minAttr - The list of attributes values of areas for the min constraint.
      minLowerBound - The lower bound of the min constraint
      minUpperBound - The upper bound of the min constraint
      maxAttr - The list of attributes values of areas for the max constraint.
      maxLowerBound - The lower bound of the max constraint
      maxUpperBound - The upper bound of the max constraint
      avgAttr - The list of attributes values of areas for the avg constraint.
      avgLowerBound - The lower bound of the avg constraint
      avgUpperBound - The upper bound of the avg constraint
      sumAttr - The list of attributes values of areas for the summation constraint.
      sumLowerBound - The lower bound of the sum constraint
      sumUpperBound - The upper bound of the sum constraint
      countLowerBound - The lower bound of the count constraint
      countUpperBound - The upper bound of the count constraint
